==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Serrature
<hw>Ser"ra*ture</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>serratura</ets> a sawing, fr. <ets>serrare</ets> to saw.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A notching, like that between the teeth of a saw, in
the edge of anything.</def> <rj><au>Martyn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of the teeth in a serrated edge; a
serration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Serricated</ent>⟦br⟧
